adjectives.description: memoried (comparative more memoried, superlative most memoried)

entries.meaning: (poetic, literary or computing, in combination) Having a memory (of a given kind).
examples: Recently, such price-reduction strategies have been replaced by a stable pricing system for our much more powerful, large-memoried machines of today.

entries.meaning: (obsolete, poetic, literary) Memorized, committed to memory.
examples: And yet I never look on midnight sky, / But I behold thine eyes' well memoried light [...].
